headline: Stocks in 2025, Warren Buffett's last day, Nike shares: 3 Things
summary: US stock futures (ES=F, NQ=F, YM=F) are hovering slightly above the flatline as equities look to close out the final trading day of 2025 — and the year in total — on a high note. Berkshire Hathaway (BRK-A, BRK-B) CEO Warren Buffett is set to step down from his chief executive role when the clock strikes midnight tonight, handing the leadership reins over to Greg Abel. Buffett will stay on as Berkshire's chairman. Nike (NKE) CEO Elliott Hill buys $1 million worth of shares in the sports apparel giant. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.

headline: Nike CEO Buys $1 Million of Stock as Insiders Bet on a Turnaround
summary: Nike  stock slumped in 2025 as it continued a multiyear downturn.  A Form 4 filed Tuesday with the Securities and Exchange Commission shows President and CEO Elliott Hill bought 16,388 shares of the sportswear company for about $61.10 apiece on Dec. 29.  The transaction boosted his direct holdings to 241,587 Class B shares, valued at nearly $14.8 million based on Tuesday’s closing price of $61.19.
